This paper presents a benchmark suite for tensor computations, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, given the focus on performance optimization and parallelism, it is most likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of state-of-the-art tensor formats and reference tensor kernel implementations suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms, which could also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) due to the use of performance models, Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) due to the mention of machine learning applications, and Machine Learning (cs.LG) due to the range of applications mentioned.
